02:07.381 --> 02:09.847
Let's go, muscles.

02:14.432 --> 02:16.815
- Hey! Where do you think you're going?! Huh?
- Ah!

02:16.816 --> 02:18.548
- Go! Go!
- Open this door, woman! So help me God!

02:18.549 --> 02:21.598
Open the bloody door!

02:23.750 --> 02:26.232
Go, mom! Drive!

02:48.331 --> 02:50.615
There'll be no green bottles

02:50.616 --> 02:52.647
Standing on the wall

02:54.016 --> 02:56.016
10 blue bottles

02:56.017 --> 02:57.615
Standing on the wall...

03:46.067 --> 03:48.931
Ah, look at that.

03:58.364 --> 04:00.448
Oi, Jimmy!

04:00.449 --> 04:03.065
Come back here.
Goofy, get back here!

04:04.466 --> 04:07.031
Can you go get your
brother, please?

04:10.298 --> 04:12.716
Nuh-uh. No way, kiddo.

04:12.717 --> 04:16.363
I've got a job interview in Albany
and it's still a day's drive away.

04:16.365 --> 04:18.363
Albany's gonna suck.

04:18.365 --> 04:20.348
And it's not going to
have waves like that.

04:20.349 --> 04:22.231
You could find a job here easy.

04:22.232 --> 04:25.081
Andrew, I'm not going
to ask you again.

04:33.632 --> 04:36.966
Come on, it's a sign.

04:36.967 --> 04:39.215
We'll fit right in.

04:39.216 --> 04:41.549
I promise.

04:44.116 --> 04:46.632
<i>Aww!</i>

04:46.633 --> 04:50.531
- <i>Big boy, let's go! Hit him!</i>
- Say it again, I dare you!

04:50.532 --> 04:53.849
I'm all ears, mate. Got
anything else you want to add?

04:53.850 --> 04:56.365
Come on, Lincoln!

04:56.366 --> 04:59.049
Nah, I didn't think so.

04:59.050 --> 05:02.098
Go on then, piss off back to Sydney

05:02.099 --> 05:03.631
<i>dickhead.</i>

05:05.915 --> 05:08.781
Awww!

05:08.782 --> 05:10.966
<i>Boys, break it up!</i>

05:10.967 --> 05:13.481
You lads break it up!

05:13.482 --> 05:16.248
Get off of him!

05:16.249 --> 05:19.214
God! Nothin' but trouble, you lot.

05:46.198 --> 05:48.032
I'll be back in an hour.

05:48.033 --> 05:51.432
Don't even think about
going anywhere.

05:51.433 --> 05:54.031
We'll talk about this then.

06:01.265 --> 06:03.198
Feel like a quick wave?

06:08.549 --> 06:11.332
<i>Deep down in Louisiana
close to New Orleans</i>

06:11.333 --> 06:14.381
<i>Way back up in the woods
among the Evergreens</i>

06:14.382 --> 06:17.148
<i>There stood a log cabin
made of earth and wood</i>

06:17.149 --> 06:18.315
<i>Where lived a country boy...</i>

06:18.316 --> 06:20.548
Hey there. I'm Gus.

06:20.549 --> 06:22.998
Jimmy Kelly.

06:23.699 --> 06:26.815
How's it goin', fellas?
<i>It's a bit nippy, eh?</i>

06:26.816 --> 06:29.281
Be warmer back on land, mate.

06:29.282 --> 06:31.564
<i>Go, Johnny, go go...</i>

06:31.565 --> 06:34.430
Guess I'll see you when I see you.

06:35.966 --> 06:38.398
Oi, wait your turn!

06:38.999 --> 06:41.631
<i>Johnny B. Goode...</i>

06:42.298 --> 06:45.431
<i>He used to carry his
guitar in a gunny sack</i>

06:45.432 --> 06:46.698
<i>Go sit beneath the tree...</i>

06:46.699 --> 06:48.265
Whoo!

06:48.266 --> 06:50.598
<i>Oh, the engineers would see
him sitting in the shade</i>

06:50.599 --> 06:54.032
<i>Strumming with the rhythm
that the drivers made</i>

06:54.033 --> 06:56.582
<i>People passing by,
they would stop and say</i>

06:56.583 --> 06:59.580
<i>"Oh my, that little country
boy could play..."</i>

08:26.014 --> 08:28.415
Wow.

08:28.416 --> 08:30.415
Hello, Mr. Fix-it.

08:30.416 --> 08:32.063
Oh, just basic patching, glassing.

08:32.065 --> 08:34.081
Caravans and canoes and stuff.

08:34.082 --> 08:35.563
<i>The nearest ding-fixer's in perth,</i>

08:35.565 --> 08:37.798
so I do most of the
locals' boards as well.

08:37.799 --> 08:39.115
Cool.

08:39.116 --> 08:42.899
- Really?
- Yeah. It's unreal.

08:42.900 --> 08:48.313
Sweet. All right, let's
take a look at ya.

08:50.981 --> 08:52.981
The nose section's pretty stuffed.

08:52.982 --> 08:55.815
I can try and bog her up, but I'm not
too sure how good she'll turn out.

08:55.816 --> 08:57.947
Why don't we just chop it off?

08:57.948 --> 09:00.114
He did.

09:02.315 --> 09:04.748
Yeah, genius.

09:04.749 --> 09:08.432
That's Dick Brewer. Bloke's a legend.
Probably has dozens of boards.

09:08.433 --> 09:11.248
- <i>So?</i>
- So we've only got the one.

09:11.249 --> 09:14.214
What if we stuff it up? I'm already
in a enough shit with mom.

09:14.215 --> 09:15.815
Couldn't make it any worse.

09:15.816 --> 09:20.448
Sorta makes sense. Less
surface area, less drag.

09:20.449 --> 09:22.764
<i>Your board, but.</i>

09:38.131 --> 09:39.580
Whoa!

09:42.515 --> 09:46.780
Pointing it the right way?
Ya little mullet.

09:56.698 --> 09:59.814
No, Jim, no, no, no,
no, not that one. Jim!

10:03.698 --> 10:05.280
Jimmy!

10:25.682 --> 10:30.497
Whoo!

10:32.098 --> 10:34.464
Whoo!

10:51.381 --> 10:54.031
And for the first time in
the history of the comp',

10:54.032 --> 10:56.098
we've scored ourselves a sponsor!

10:58.266 --> 11:00.732
Which means finally someone
else gets the privilege

11:00.733 --> 11:02.565
of putting on the keg.

11:02.566 --> 11:05.632
And that someone is
Mr. Ocean King himself,

11:05.633 --> 11:07.615
Gordon king!

11:07.616 --> 11:10.848
- Over to you, Gordo.
- All right.

11:10.849 --> 11:12.731
Thanks, Ron.

11:12.732 --> 11:16.231
Look, Ocean King are
stoked to be here,

11:16.232 --> 11:19.531
<i>supporting surfing at a grassroots
level in Western Australia.</i>

11:19.532 --> 11:21.581
By now you've all seen
candy wandering around.

11:21.582 --> 11:23.582
Where are you, darlin'?
Now come on, come over here.

11:23.583 --> 11:26.598
Right? Ha ha ha!

11:26.599 --> 11:28.198
Look at that, eh?

11:28.199 --> 11:30.065
If you're nice to her,
she might even give you

11:30.066 --> 11:32.232
a free stick of Ocean
King surfboard wax.

11:32.233 --> 11:34.348
I'll give her a stick!

11:34.349 --> 11:36.749
Yeah, right on, mate.
Back in your box.

11:36.750 --> 11:39.548
I can tell we all want to have a
beer, so let's get on with it.

11:39.549 --> 11:43.364
Okay, the winner of
the 1972 Ocean King

11:43.365 --> 11:44.914
Seacliffe Amateur Surf Comp'

11:44.915 --> 11:48.348
on what I am told is his
trademark red rocket,

11:48.349 --> 11:50.848
it's Jimmy Kelly!

11:50.849 --> 11:53.881
<i>Come up here, son! You got it!</i>

11:55.082 --> 11:56.815
Ah, shit!

11:56.816 --> 11:59.582
- Oh!
- Whoo!

11:59.583 --> 12:03.332
- Yeah!
- Speech! Speech!

12:03.333 --> 12:05.864
Well...

12:05.865 --> 12:08.682
- Let's get pissed!
- Yeah!

12:33.299 --> 12:35.531
<i>Ah, slow down a bit, mate.</i>

12:35.532 --> 12:37.864
Anyone'd think you got
somewhere else to go.

12:37.865 --> 12:39.648
Yeah, wind's going
off-shore, Percy.

12:39.649 --> 12:41.998
Be clean as a whistle
out there right now.

12:41.999 --> 12:44.499
I knock this one off, I'll get
half an hour in the water

12:44.500 --> 12:46.348
before the sharks
come out and eat me.

12:46.349 --> 12:48.081
Rather you than me, mate.

12:49.683 --> 12:52.665
Come on, Percy! Chop chop!

12:52.666 --> 12:56.163
You old bag of bones!
You're not done yet, mate.

12:57.364 --> 12:59.448
<i>Hang in there, Andy.</i>

12:59.449 --> 13:02.332
You won't have to carry the
old bugger for much longer.

13:02.333 --> 13:03.914
He's been carrying me
long enough, Stan.

13:03.915 --> 13:06.831
He probably deserves a bit of a
breather by now, don't you reckon?

13:06.832 --> 13:10.731
Aw, you're a soft touch. Plenty of time
for that when he's not on the clock.

13:10.732 --> 13:13.948
- Right, Percy?
- Oh, right as rain, Stan.

13:13.949 --> 13:17.315
About bloody time.

13:17.316 --> 13:19.549
You were supposed to
be here this morning!

13:19.550 --> 13:23.029
You blokes don't mind working
back to unload it, do you?

13:38.065 --> 13:40.515
<i>Hey, Jimmy!</i>

13:40.516 --> 13:42.348
Ah. Hey, ladies.

13:42.349 --> 13:44.598
- <i>How you doin'?</i>
- Nice car.

13:44.599 --> 13:47.197
Ah, thanks.

13:49.398 --> 13:51.931
Nice bike.

14:18.598 --> 14:20.015
<i>Hey, you.</i>

14:20.016 --> 14:23.581
Goofy, you smelly
old bastard, mate.

14:38.398 --> 14:40.398
Jesus, I thought my day sucked.

14:40.399 --> 14:43.048
I'm just finishing up.

14:43.049 --> 14:46.146
<i>So? How'd he go?</i>

14:52.566 --> 14:54.831
I thought we were going
to fix mom's car?

14:54.832 --> 14:57.065
Oh, shit, I totally forgot.

14:57.066 --> 14:59.314
- I'm meeting the boys for a drink.
- Which boys?

14:59.315 --> 15:01.547
I don't know, just the usual.

15:03.215 --> 15:04.864
How was your day?

15:04.865 --> 15:06.631
Long.

15:08.148 --> 15:10.315
You're really not going
to ask how it went.

15:10.316 --> 15:11.946
How what went?

15:13.565 --> 15:15.415
Dickhead!

15:15.416 --> 15:17.565
- Mom told you, didn't she?
- She couldn't help herself, mate.

15:17.566 --> 15:21.282
- Ahh! Jimmy Kelly!
- Whooo!

15:21.283 --> 15:23.232
<i>How good is that, mate?</i>

15:23.233 --> 15:25.564
Now you make it to the nationals, I'm
going to ask Stan for the day off.

15:25.565 --> 15:26.964
- How's that?
- Yeah, right.

15:26.965 --> 15:29.163
I'll believe that when I see it.

15:30.381 --> 15:33.614
I'll fix the car on the
weekend. I promise.

15:43.331 --> 15:45.147
Fuckin' hell.

15:55.897 --> 16:00.098
<i>Whoa, thought it was a nightmare</i>

16:00.099 --> 16:02.863
<i>Lo, it's all so true</i>

16:04.065 --> 16:07.081
<i>They told me, "don't
go walkin' slow</i>

16:07.082 --> 16:10.498
<i>The devil's on the loose"</i>

16:10.499 --> 16:13.647
<i>Better run through the jungle</i>

16:13.648 --> 16:17.298
<i>Better run through the jungle</i>

16:17.299 --> 16:20.881
<i>Better run through the jungle</i>

16:20.882 --> 16:23.913
<i>whoa, don't look back to see...</i>

16:41.131 --> 16:44.298
You boys know the fine for
pilfering another man's crayfish?

16:44.299 --> 16:46.064
<i>It's 10 bucks...</i>

16:46.065 --> 16:48.081
Per cray.

16:48.082 --> 16:49.896
<i>How many you got?</i>

16:54.998 --> 16:57.464
That's 20 bucks right there, mate.

16:59.781 --> 17:01.947
Honestly, we're really sorry, mate.

17:04.630 --> 17:07.896
Yeah, well, you will be if
the owner ever catches you.

17:10.898 --> 17:13.047
I can't believe you get
away with living like this.

17:13.048 --> 17:14.814
Who's gonna stop me?

17:14.815 --> 17:18.047
I don't know. Movin'
around all the time...

17:18.048 --> 17:20.931
Taking surf photographs,

17:20.932 --> 17:24.597
not knowing where you're gonna
be one day to the next?

17:24.598 --> 17:26.931
Doesn't seem like a job, right?

17:26.932 --> 17:29.681
It's not. It's not a job.

17:29.682 --> 17:32.248
Look, I surf and I
get to document it.

17:32.249 --> 17:34.531
If some idiot wants to
put diesel in my bus

17:34.532 --> 17:39.514
and buy me a plane ticket,
sweet, but it's not a job.

17:39.515 --> 17:41.746
Hey.

17:44.648 --> 17:46.648
Just don't tell anyone.

17:46.649 --> 17:48.514
G'day.

17:48.515 --> 17:50.414
- Hey.
- Where'd you come from?

17:50.415 --> 17:53.065
I was surfing that little
left-hander off the point.

17:53.066 --> 17:55.098
What's that called again?

17:55.099 --> 17:57.979
- Um, lefties.
- Of course.

18:06.631 --> 18:09.915
So let me guess. What,
Southern California, right?

18:09.916 --> 18:12.564
<i>Malibu?</i>

18:12.565 --> 18:16.232
Hawaii, west coast of Oahu.

18:16.233 --> 18:19.414
So what happened? You get sick
of warm water and perfect waves?

18:19.415 --> 18:22.098
- Something like that.
- <i>Huh.</i>

18:22.099 --> 18:24.996
How long you and your
boyfriend in town for?

18:26.564 --> 18:28.265
J.B.'s not my boyfriend.

18:28.266 --> 18:31.063
He's my dad's friend.

18:31.564 --> 18:34.981
Uh, dad wasn't too
stoked with the boys

18:34.982 --> 18:36.881
I was hanging out
with on the island,

18:36.882 --> 18:39.497
so he asked J.B. If I could
tag along for a few months.

18:39.498 --> 18:41.464
Figured it might straighten me out.

18:41.465 --> 18:44.929
What, he actually thought hanging
with J.B. Might straighten you out?

18:46.730 --> 18:50.096
- Should have seen the other boys.
- <i>Which other boys?</i>

18:51.898 --> 18:54.065
Jimmy Kelly.

18:54.066 --> 18:56.764
Hey, I'm Lani.

18:56.765 --> 18:59.015
- Yes, you are.
- Oh.

18:59.016 --> 19:01.114
Look, I don't know how long
you guys are around for,

19:01.115 --> 19:02.697
but if you ever want to check
out some of the local breaks,

19:02.698 --> 19:05.539
- I'd be happy to show youse around.
- Sounds good. Thanks.

19:05.540 --> 19:07.331
<i>And once you've done
the tourist trap,</i>

19:07.332 --> 19:09.198
I'll show you a few spots
even he doesn't know about.

19:09.199 --> 19:12.364
<i>- Is that right, superstar?</i>
- Yeah, well, I'd take you too, mate,

19:12.365 --> 19:13.948
but it's a bit heavy for beginners.

19:13.949 --> 19:16.064
Oh, turn it up, mate.

19:16.065 --> 19:19.082
There you go... it does work.

19:19.083 --> 19:22.414
Okay, uh, there you go.

19:22.415 --> 19:24.764
Thanks, man.

19:24.765 --> 19:27.764
- <i>These all yours?</i>
- Yeah.

19:27.765 --> 19:29.198
Shit. Where haven't you surfed?

19:29.199 --> 19:32.031
Grajagan's. It's a
real fast left-hander.

19:32.032 --> 19:34.447
Sucks real dry, bowls you real big.

19:34.448 --> 19:38.330
Yeah, only a handful
have ever surfed there.

19:38.331 --> 19:40.831
Yeah, some American cat...
He found it.

19:40.832 --> 19:42.664
Don't know how, 'cause
it's right there

19:42.665 --> 19:44.581
in the jungles of Indonesia.

19:44.582 --> 19:48.697
Filled with scorpions,
tigers, monkeys,

19:48.698 --> 19:50.664
<i>other crazy shit.</i>

19:50.665 --> 19:53.931
Wow, sounds like a total
mission just to get there.

19:53.932 --> 19:57.114
Yeah, well, the best
ones usually are, mate.

19:57.115 --> 19:59.215
That's the trip right there, man.

19:59.216 --> 20:03.314
If God surfed, that would
be his home break.

20:11.664 --> 20:15.680
That is exactly what
she was wearing, man.

20:15.681 --> 20:17.598
Yeah, from the sounds of her,
I'm surprised you even noticed.

20:17.599 --> 20:19.031
<i>Nice one, Gus.</i>

20:19.032 --> 20:20.698
<i>"With sculptured arms for paddling,</i>

20:20.699 --> 20:23.231
velcro neck and snap
fasteners for the cold,

20:23.232 --> 20:24.929
it's just for surfers."

20:26.581 --> 20:30.114
That's just for millionaire
surfers, more like it.

20:30.115 --> 20:32.548
Who's got 60 bucks lying around?

20:32.549 --> 20:35.981
We'll be dead and buried by the
time it makes it down here.

20:35.982 --> 20:37.879
Who cares?

20:39.981 --> 20:42.548
- Hey, mom?
- <i>I'm not here.</i>

20:42.549 --> 20:44.214
Got a sec?

20:50.115 --> 20:52.013
<i>Hey!</i>

20:54.048 --> 20:55.280
<i>Hey!</i>

20:55.281 --> 20:58.280
<i>Check it out! It's Rubberman!</i>

20:58.281 --> 20:59.864
Jeez, aren't you embarrassed?

20:59.865 --> 21:02.381
No. Why should I be?

21:02.382 --> 21:03.948
He was talking to your board, mate.

21:03.949 --> 21:06.630
Hey, boys.

21:06.631 --> 21:08.931
Great swell, boys.
You're not going in?

21:08.932 --> 21:10.998
Yeah, it's bloody cold, eh?

21:10.999 --> 21:13.614
- Yeah.
- Freezing, isn't it? Brrr!

21:13.615 --> 21:14.915
Yeah.

21:14.916 --> 21:17.612
Yeah.

21:43.214 --> 21:44.712
<i>Hey!</i>

21:47.348 --> 21:49.947
<i>Hey!</i>

21:49.948 --> 21:52.614
Fair go.

21:52.615 --> 21:54.947
Turn that thing off,
put your feet up, mom.

21:54.948 --> 21:56.281
Nearly done.

21:56.282 --> 21:58.347
"Mark 2." What do you think?

22:00.314 --> 22:03.581
I might struggle to
squeeze into it.

22:03.582 --> 22:06.814
Mick Harris saw Jimmy's one and
asked if we'd make one for his son.

22:06.815 --> 22:09.514
- Well, tell him to make his own wetsuit.
- Said he'd pay $15.

22:09.515 --> 22:11.214
- 15 bucks.
- Mm-hmm.

22:11.215 --> 22:14.580
Well, what are you
waiting for? Sew, woman!

22:16.148 --> 22:18.696
You in there, Jimbo?

22:20.048 --> 22:22.514
Jimmy, let's fix this car.

22:35.597 --> 22:37.697
What the hell?

22:44.280 --> 22:46.147
Haven't seen Jimmy, have you, Ron?

22:46.148 --> 22:48.081
Yeah, he was here a
couple hours ago.

22:48.082 --> 22:51.581
Said he was headed home.
Everything all right?

22:51.582 --> 22:53.914
Yeah.

22:53.915 --> 22:55.880
Yeah, sweet as.

24:08.131 --> 24:11.563
Ah, Jesus! Get back here!

24:11.564 --> 24:13.930
Stop! What are you doing?!

24:27.664 --> 24:30.446
- What the fuck are you doing?
- Andy.

24:31.614 --> 24:33.964
- Give me a hand, quick!
- Fuck!

24:36.365 --> 24:38.815
Thanks, man.

24:38.816 --> 24:40.948
You stay away from
my fuckin' brother.

24:40.949 --> 24:42.781
<i>Open this bloody door!</i>

24:42.782 --> 24:46.713
<i>Here! Police!</i>

24:52.681 --> 24:54.981
You got to take it all back,

24:54.982 --> 24:57.681
leave it outside the cop
shop with a little note

24:57.682 --> 24:59.514
saying who it belonged to.

24:59.515 --> 25:01.914
Yeah, right.

25:09.113 --> 25:12.345
Do it or don't bother coming back.

25:27.297 --> 25:30.997
Percy started working for my
father straight out of school,

25:30.998 --> 25:33.864
- and that was 1920...?
- Two.

25:33.865 --> 25:38.464
'22. Since then, well, he's become
part of the fabric of the place.

25:38.465 --> 25:42.915
<i>So in honor of 50 years of
hard work and dedication,</i>

25:42.916 --> 25:46.080
I'd like to present him with a
small token of our appreciation.

25:46.081 --> 25:49.231
- <i>Well done, Perce.</i>
- All right!

25:49.232 --> 25:52.796
<i>Speech! Give us a speech, Perce.</i>

25:55.313 --> 25:57.164
Thanks.

25:57.165 --> 26:00.714
- <i>Good on ya.</i>
- Yay! Love you, mate.

26:00.715 --> 26:03.197
Well, that's it, gentlemen.
Back to work. Thank you.

26:22.908 --> 26:26.431
<i>Mrs. Kelly, you look
absolutely fantastic.</i>

26:27.965 --> 26:29.447
<i>I wish my mom dressed like you.</i>

26:29.448 --> 26:32.564
<i>Oh, thanks. You want
some more salad?</i>

26:32.565 --> 26:33.597
<i>Yeah.</i>

26:33.598 --> 26:35.913
Good size flatty.

26:35.914 --> 26:39.530
I'm surprised you had time to go
fishing, considering your busy schedule.

26:39.531 --> 26:43.862
Had to go into town,
drop a bunch of stuff off.

26:46.431 --> 26:48.662
Caught 'em after that.

26:57.132 --> 26:58.598
- Howdy, Gus.
- Yeah, hi, Andy.

26:58.599 --> 27:00.531
- How you goin'?
- <i>Yeah, good.</i>

27:00.532 --> 27:01.698
What's the occasion?

27:01.699 --> 27:04.697
Mr. O'Reilly offered me
a promotion, didn't he?

27:04.698 --> 27:07.014
Hey, nice one, mate.

27:07.015 --> 27:08.980
- <i>That's unreal.</i>
- Yeah.

27:08.981 --> 27:11.947
More bucks, more hours...
The whole nine yards.

27:11.948 --> 27:15.247
Aw, that's fantastic, love.
When do you start?

27:15.248 --> 27:17.462
Well, I don't.

27:18.664 --> 27:22.546
I told him to shove it.

27:23.697 --> 27:26.147
It's all right. I've
got another plan.

27:26.148 --> 27:27.997
Is it legal?

27:27.998 --> 27:31.930
Yup. It's been staring us in
the face the whole time...

27:31.931 --> 27:34.329
The whole bloody time.

27:58.197 --> 28:02.296
<i>Rockin' and rollin',
you're still doing it now</i>

28:04.013 --> 28:08.096
<i>15 years today and
you remember how</i>

28:10.030 --> 28:13.880
<i>You're gonna hear it now
blastin' out your radio...</i>

28:16.981 --> 28:18.780
Look at this, will you?

28:18.781 --> 28:22.129
- It's a well-oiled machine.
- Hardly.

28:27.430 --> 28:29.163
Any luck?

28:29.164 --> 28:31.664
Not yet.

28:31.665 --> 28:33.780
Look on the bright side...

28:33.781 --> 28:35.913
At least we won't have to
buy surf gear ever again.

28:35.914 --> 28:37.097
Hmm!

28:44.280 --> 28:46.680
- <i>How you goin', Greg?</i>
- All right.

28:46.681 --> 28:49.297
- What do you reckon?
- Bit short, aren't they?

28:49.298 --> 28:52.430
That's the idea. That's what
they're doing back east.

28:52.431 --> 28:53.833
- Yeah?
- Yeah, she's a 6'8"...

28:53.834 --> 28:55.930
perfect for a bloke your size.

28:55.931 --> 28:59.414
- How much?
- Aw, 35.

28:59.415 --> 29:02.131
Call it an even 50
with the wetsuit.

29:02.132 --> 29:03.747
Look, mate, you don't like it,

29:03.748 --> 29:05.613
I'll give you your money
back, no questions asked.

29:05.614 --> 29:07.180
And you can keep the wettie.

29:07.181 --> 29:10.296
- You're cocky, aren't you?
- I've ridden it.

29:18.130 --> 29:20.197
All right, you're on.

29:20.198 --> 29:23.347
Good man. I'll give you a hand.

29:23.348 --> 29:27.064
Looks like we just beat the rush.

29:29.132 --> 29:31.129
- How are ya?
- Hey, how are ya?

29:38.447 --> 29:40.297
- He's a natural.
- Pleasure doing business.

29:40.298 --> 29:41.680
- Thanks.
- See ya.

29:41.681 --> 29:43.347
See ya.

29:43.348 --> 29:46.580
- See you later, boys.
- See ya, Jim.

29:46.581 --> 29:48.280
Man, you can talk.

29:48.281 --> 29:50.997
Lookin' good, Gus!

29:50.998 --> 29:52.347
Yeah.

29:56.080 --> 29:59.079
Be right out.

30:02.947 --> 30:04.480
Aloha.

30:04.481 --> 30:06.214
Oh, hey.

30:06.215 --> 30:08.097
How's it going?
You settling in okay?

30:08.098 --> 30:10.964
You know, just getting my bearings.

30:10.965 --> 30:12.464
What, all two streets?

30:14.947 --> 30:17.247
- You in the market for a new stick?
- Maybe.

30:17.248 --> 30:20.946
I really just came to see Jimmy's
set-up, see what all the hype's about.

30:20.947 --> 30:22.381
Jimmy's set-up? Is that right?

30:22.382 --> 30:25.447
C'mon, mate. I am head shaper.

30:25.448 --> 30:28.447
Well, you're the only
shaper, dickhead.

30:28.448 --> 30:31.696
I get him to put the bins out,
sweep up, that kind of thing.

30:31.697 --> 30:33.464
- Keeps him off the streets.
- Don't worry about him.

30:33.465 --> 30:35.264
- Reckons he taught me everything I know.
- I did, mate.

30:35.265 --> 30:37.997
Just not everything
I know. Big difference.

30:37.998 --> 30:40.697
Uh, we're going to check
out the canyons later.

30:40.698 --> 30:42.863
Think it'll handle the big stuff?

30:42.864 --> 30:44.947
Why don't you borrow
it and find out?

30:44.948 --> 30:47.247
Oh, no, I couldn't do that.

30:47.248 --> 30:49.347
- Wouldn't feel comfortable.
- Why not?

30:49.348 --> 30:50.947
You know your way around a wave.

30:50.948 --> 30:52.980
Go for it. You're not
going to steal it.

30:52.981 --> 30:55.097
Promise you'll pick it
up whenever you need to?

30:55.098 --> 30:56.630
Scout's honor.

30:56.631 --> 30:59.330
I'll even swing by and
pick it up personally.

30:59.331 --> 31:00.997
- Ha.
- Okay.

31:00.998 --> 31:03.696
Well, I'll let you
know how it goes then.

31:03.697 --> 31:05.097
- Okay.
- Later.

31:05.098 --> 31:06.530
See ya.

31:13.447 --> 31:15.112
"Scout's honor"?

31:15.980 --> 31:17.481
What?

31:17.482 --> 31:19.481
No wonder you're single.

31:19.482 --> 31:22.147
You're kidding me, aren't you? She
couldn't take her eyes off me.

31:22.148 --> 31:24.147
Yeah, she was trying to work out

31:24.148 --> 31:26.513
if you were my brother or my dad.

31:28.147 --> 31:29.913
Go play, Jimbo.

31:29.914 --> 31:33.397
Oi! Drinks all around!

31:33.398 --> 31:35.131
Dream on, fellas.

31:35.132 --> 31:36.730
- Maybe next time.
- Aww!

31:36.731 --> 31:38.397
So what do you reckon?

31:38.398 --> 31:40.663
Sensible thing would be to put
it back in the mortgage, right?

31:40.664 --> 31:43.030
I don't know. I guess.

31:43.031 --> 31:45.263
Then next month we're
back to square one.

31:46.630 --> 31:48.764
<i>But if we bought, say, a planer,</i>

31:48.765 --> 31:50.714
<i>made some templates,</i>

31:50.715 --> 31:52.630
- a sander...
- Electric sander?

31:52.631 --> 31:54.297
Electric sander, a ton of resin...

31:54.298 --> 31:55.630
- Some fiberglass.
- What do you reckon?

31:55.631 --> 31:58.878
Eh? Why not, mate?

31:59.514 --> 32:02.364
Oh, ho ho! There's a rare sight.

32:02.365 --> 32:04.696
The Kelly gang out on the town.

32:04.697 --> 32:06.464
- Ha. Hi, Jim.
- Miller.

32:06.465 --> 32:09.097
Andrew. Buy you a beer?

32:09.098 --> 32:10.096
Naw, just leaving, actually.

32:10.097 --> 32:11.696
Oh, fuckin' turn it up.

32:11.697 --> 32:14.263
Ron, another beer for Andrew here.

32:14.264 --> 32:16.181
What's big brother letting
you drink these days, hmm?

32:16.182 --> 32:18.480
- Whatever I want.
- Oh, whatever he wants.

32:18.481 --> 32:19.579
Thanks, Ron.

32:19.580 --> 32:21.263
Aw, come on, hang around.

32:21.264 --> 32:22.997
We're short a few sheilas.

32:22.998 --> 32:25.397
You're the one wearing the tassels.

32:25.398 --> 32:27.596
Like 'em, do you?

32:27.597 --> 32:30.729
Made 'em for myself in prison.

32:30.730 --> 32:32.613
Well, the cut really suits you.

32:32.614 --> 32:34.080
It's very slimming.

32:34.081 --> 32:36.497
Is that right?

32:36.498 --> 32:38.964
Why don't I take it off and
give you a closer look?

32:38.965 --> 32:41.414
Calm down now, Miller. Take it
outside if you want to muck around.

32:41.415 --> 32:42.997
It's okay, Ron.

32:42.998 --> 32:44.797
Leave 'em to their little shindig.

32:46.448 --> 32:50.513
Round of shandies for the boys.

32:51.314 --> 32:53.845
Eh? Let's go, Jim.

33:07.997 --> 33:09.930
<i>Andrew, how much are we
talking about exactly?</i>

33:09.931 --> 33:13.280
I don't know. Five
grand, kick it off.

33:13.281 --> 33:16.713
5,000... dollars?

33:16.714 --> 33:18.563
Yeah, just for starters.

33:21.529 --> 33:24.663
Son, you're dreaming.

33:24.664 --> 33:29.180
I'm not going to lend $500
on a whim, let alone $5,000.

33:29.181 --> 33:31.397
And given the state of
your mom's mortgage,

33:31.398 --> 33:35.364
I don't think now's the right time to
be getting further into debt, do you?

33:35.365 --> 33:37.529
You just can't drift through life

33:37.530 --> 33:39.197
like it owes you a living, Andrew.

33:39.198 --> 33:40.813
It doesn't.

33:40.814 --> 33:43.947
My advice? Head over to the mill

33:43.948 --> 33:47.264
and ask Stan O'Reilly
for your old job back.

33:47.265 --> 33:49.495
At least it's real.

33:51.280 --> 33:53.563
<i>You're the only
supplier in the state,</i>

33:53.564 --> 33:55.797
<i>so I'm hardly going to
screw you over, am I?</i>

33:55.798 --> 33:58.313
<i>You'll have your money
by the end of the month.</i>

33:58.314 --> 34:00.863
Bob, I guarantee it, okay?

34:00.864 --> 34:04.596
I just need a few blanks on tick
to get me into the game, mate.

34:04.597 --> 34:07.796
I don't know. How's 20 sound?

34:07.797 --> 34:10.429
<i>Yeah.</i>

34:11.297 --> 34:13.246
Fantastic. All right.

34:13.248 --> 34:15.245
Great, see you then.

34:16.480 --> 34:18.246
20 blanks on credit?

34:18.248 --> 34:20.596
I must have sounded like I actually
knew what I was talking about.

34:20.597 --> 34:23.097
All those years of bullshitting
might finally be paying off.

34:23.098 --> 34:26.246
Come check this out.

34:33.880 --> 34:35.713
<i>What in Christ's name is this?</i>

34:35.714 --> 34:38.562
It's a knee-board for Gus.

34:39.614 --> 34:42.197
- Um, J.B.'s idea.
- You serious?

34:42.197 --> 34:44.513
It's an early Christmas present.

34:44.514 --> 34:46.014
You can't leave him
on the beach all day.

34:46.014 --> 34:48.547
The little bastard would
steal all my gear.

34:51.098 --> 34:54.963
We made something for you too.

34:58.947 --> 35:00.679
Whoo!

35:02.763 --> 35:04.862
Whoo!

35:09.146 --> 35:12.997
<i>Oh</i>

35:12.998 --> 35:16.279
<i>It's all about her</i>

35:17.380 --> 35:20.196
<i>Oh</i>

35:20.197 --> 35:24.413
<i>It's all about her</i>

35:24.414 --> 35:26.713
<i>I love her love, she's
been so kind to me</i>

35:26.714 --> 35:29.113
<i>She's opened up my eyes...</i>

35:29.114 --> 35:31.162
Whoo!

35:32.362 --> 35:34.063
<i>The whispers and the summer wine</i>

35:34.064 --> 35:37.229
<i>May have made me realize</i>

35:38.830 --> 35:42.097
<i>Whoo oooo</i>

35:42.098 --> 35:45.997
<i>It's not about her</i>

35:45.998 --> 35:49.997
<i>Ooo ooo ooo ooo</i>

35:49.998 --> 35:53.179
<i>It's all about her.</i>

35:57.297 --> 35:58.446
Hey!

35:58.447 --> 36:00.164
How's the new board,
huh? Rips, yeah?

36:00.165 --> 36:01.713
Oh, man, it's responsive.

36:01.714 --> 36:03.446
I can feel it in my
bum ankle already.

36:03.447 --> 36:05.496
Almost ate it a couple
of times out there.

36:05.497 --> 36:08.180
It'd do you good to get out of
control every now and then.

36:08.181 --> 36:10.164
Hey, did you see that?
Did you see that?

36:10.165 --> 36:11.796
Man, this thing is unbelievable.

36:11.797 --> 36:14.214
Man, honestly, it's the
best present ever. It is.

36:14.215 --> 36:16.563
- Yeah.
- You're making it look too easy!

36:16.564 --> 36:19.846
I think it's less about me
and more about the board.

36:19.847 --> 36:22.281
I'll have to make the next one
even more radical then, huh?

36:22.282 --> 36:23.946
- Steady on, tiger.
- Huh?

36:23.947 --> 36:25.946
That's awesome for
surfers that can rip.

36:25.947 --> 36:27.647
Don't forget about the
rest of the world too.

36:27.648 --> 36:29.797
- Bugger the rest of the world.
- No, you think about it.

36:29.798 --> 36:31.413
There's a whole bunch
of people out there

36:31.414 --> 36:33.346
waiting to surf better
because of our gear.

36:33.347 --> 36:36.696
We play our cards right, we could be
shaping a much bigger future here.

36:39.181 --> 36:41.863
Shaping a much bigger future?

36:41.864 --> 36:44.780
Yeah, it's a TV ad.

36:45.965 --> 36:50.263
You cannot beat the man by
becoming the man. Yeah?

36:50.264 --> 36:52.197
No, I'm just thinking big picture.

36:52.198 --> 36:53.930
What's wrong with that?

36:53.931 --> 36:55.930
All right, guys, good sesh.

36:55.931 --> 36:58.229
Catch you later.

37:02.163 --> 37:06.563
I'm just shaping surfboards,
brother. That's all I'm doing.

37:06.564 --> 37:08.630
Ha! Gussy!

37:15.429 --> 37:18.596
<i>Don't think I don't know
what I'm talking about</i>

37:18.597 --> 37:21.529
<i>I'm leaving you, baby,
without a doubt</i>

37:21.530 --> 37:24.180
<i>I don't need you no more</i>

37:24.181 --> 37:26.446
<i>Don't need you, baby...</i>

37:28.880 --> 37:31.413
<i>Got room for one more?</i>

37:31.414 --> 37:33.513
I brought tofu scrambles.

37:33.514 --> 37:35.013
<i>Love is all the same</i>

37:35.014 --> 37:38.396
<i>I don't need you no more</i>

37:38.397 --> 37:40.645
<i>Don't need you, baby</i>

37:42.246 --> 37:45.064
<i>You're biting off more
than you can chew</i>

37:45.065 --> 37:47.930
<i>Baby, I ain't ever
coming home to you</i>

37:47.931 --> 37:49.629
<i>I don't need you no more...</i>

37:50.831 --> 37:53.279
<i>Don't need you, baby</i>

37:55.312 --> 37:58.279
<i>Look so sweet, look so fine...</i>

37:58.280 --> 38:01.612
<i>Take your time, sweetheart!</i>

38:04.729 --> 38:06.263
Doesn't even look like me.

38:06.264 --> 38:08.480
Whoo! Yeah!

38:08.481 --> 38:11.279
So much more than just you, kid.

38:14.330 --> 38:18.546
<i>So you know everybody
that there is to know</i>

38:18.547 --> 38:20.730
<i>Puttin' on your charm
like a little show</i>

38:20.731 --> 38:23.131
<i>I don't need you no more</i>

38:23.132 --> 38:25.845
<i>Don't need you, baby...</i>

38:27.279 --> 38:30.046
- Whoo!
- Jimmy! That's you, brother!

38:30.047 --> 38:33.680
- Ho ho ho!
- <i>I don't need you no more</i>

38:33.681 --> 38:35.763
<i>Don't need you, baby</i>

38:35.764 --> 38:39.246
<i>I don't want you,
don't need you, baby</i>

38:39.247 --> 38:42.213
<i>Oh!
Don't need you, baby</i>

38:42.214 --> 38:43.779
<i>Goin' on too long</i>

38:43.780 --> 38:45.679
<i>Don't need you, baby</i>

38:45.680 --> 38:48.346
<i>Ahhhh!
Don't need you, baby</i>

38:48.347 --> 38:49.913
<i>I don't want you, baby</i>

38:49.914 --> 38:52.179
<i>Don't need you, baby</i>

38:52.180 --> 38:55.078
<i>Movin' on, don't need you, baby.</i>

39:01.679 --> 39:04.814
See, that is the trip right there.

39:07.147 --> 39:09.663
Probably surfs solo most days.

39:09.664 --> 39:12.030
<i>He's not battling for waves.</i>

39:12.031 --> 39:15.313
He's not proving himself
against anyone.

39:15.314 --> 39:17.830
<i>That's it right there... unreal.</i>

39:17.831 --> 39:20.696
You reckon? I'd get bored.

39:20.697 --> 39:23.129
How does he even
know how good he is?

39:23.130 --> 39:25.896
Who cares?

39:25.897 --> 39:29.279
Seriously, who cares? It's...

39:29.280 --> 39:32.145
I reckon the last thing
on his mind is competing.

39:32.146 --> 39:37.012
You know, hey, we're pounding up
and down the coast selling shit.

39:37.779 --> 39:40.679
He's out there.

39:42.579 --> 39:46.579
Look.

39:59.730 --> 40:01.429
Booah!

40:03.312 --> 40:06.779
<i>He's living the dream.
What are we doing?</i>

40:08.647 --> 40:11.012
You can't buy what he's got, yeah?

40:12.047 --> 40:13.929
Especially if he's not selling.

40:21.530 --> 40:23.480
Where'd you learn to do all this?

40:23.481 --> 40:25.246
Raising sons.

40:25.247 --> 40:28.413
They went through clothes
like you wouldn't believe.

40:28.414 --> 40:31.763
Just, you know, made sense
to make all our own stuff.

40:31.764 --> 40:33.313
At least they're both boys.

40:33.314 --> 40:35.079
Probably just hand
stuff down, right?

40:35.080 --> 40:36.313
Yeah, I wish.

40:36.314 --> 40:38.746
Those two, they're
like chalk and cheese

40:38.747 --> 40:41.129
when it comes to their
taste in things.

40:41.130 --> 40:43.396
- Really?
- Yeah.

40:43.397 --> 40:47.962
When they're not, look out.
It can get ugly.

40:57.896 --> 41:00.463
Didn't expect you
guys back so soon.

41:00.464 --> 41:03.629
- Manage to sell anything?
- Ta-dah!

41:03.630 --> 41:05.446
Where did it all go?

41:05.447 --> 41:07.646
Inside barrels all the way
from here to Esperance.

41:07.647 --> 41:10.279
They saw the film, went nuts.
It was like a feeding frenzy.

41:11.780 --> 41:15.095
- It's unreal, man.
- Yeah, it is.

41:18.696 --> 41:20.429
What's this?

41:20.430 --> 41:23.596
Aw, it's a little something for
getting us off the ground.

41:23.597 --> 41:25.578
Plenty more where that came from.

41:58.080 --> 42:01.313
Mmm. What time is it?

42:01.314 --> 42:03.079
A little after 3:00.

42:03.080 --> 42:05.096
I should go.

42:05.097 --> 42:08.561
You could always just stay here.

42:12.096 --> 42:14.595
Nice try, Andrew Kelly.

42:16.930 --> 42:20.445
Good luck tomorrow.

42:24.945 --> 42:26.847
<i>As you can see,</i>

42:26.848 --> 42:29.946
<i>sales projections, comparisons
with overseas competitors,</i>

42:29.947 --> 42:32.797
ideas for new products
down the line.

42:32.798 --> 42:36.913
The challenge here, Andrew, is that
you're asking for a business loan.

42:36.914 --> 42:39.446
But what you're talking
about is a leisure activity.

42:39.447 --> 42:41.530
Either way, we just sold
out our entire inventory.

42:41.531 --> 42:43.346
Out of the back of your Kombi.

42:43.347 --> 42:45.130
You said to start thinking
like a businessman.

42:45.131 --> 42:47.145
That's what you said.
That's what I'm doing.

42:47.146 --> 42:50.396
We lend to farmers
because they grow crops.

42:50.397 --> 42:52.062
<i>People need to eat.</i>

42:52.063 --> 42:55.146
Where exactly is your market?

42:55.147 --> 42:58.429
Are you kidding me? 95% of
Aussies live on the coast.

42:58.430 --> 43:01.129
Our gear makes living
on the coast better.

43:01.130 --> 43:03.496
I would have thought our market
was pretty bloody obvious.

43:03.497 --> 43:05.096
- <i>Andrew...</i>
- That's just here.

43:05.097 --> 43:07.380
Now we can reach people all
over the world, Mr. Grumley.

43:07.381 --> 43:10.713
- Look, Andrew, I hear what you're saying.
- How?

43:10.714 --> 43:13.413
I'm sorry, James?

43:13.414 --> 43:15.497
How can you hear what he's saying

43:15.498 --> 43:19.245
when you've got your head
shoved so far up your own ass?

43:27.613 --> 43:30.713
I thought that went well.

43:30.714 --> 43:32.346
Unbelievable.

43:32.347 --> 43:34.747
What? I was doing you a favor.

43:34.748 --> 43:38.280
You gotta be a farmer or a logger
to score a loan in this town.

43:38.281 --> 43:40.945
You gotta get a haircut.

43:40.946 --> 43:43.246
They're never going
to give us a red cent

43:43.247 --> 43:46.945
because we're on the
outside looking in.

43:48.379 --> 43:50.713
You know what?

43:50.714 --> 43:53.078
I'm cool with that.

44:02.063 --> 44:03.629
J.B.'s right, man.

44:03.630 --> 44:06.346
<i>You can't buy what we've got,</i>

44:06.347 --> 44:08.678
especially if we're not selling.

44:16.262 --> 44:18.430
<i>I've been wanting to bust this out</i>

44:18.431 --> 44:21.679
<i>since I got back from Indonesia.</i>

44:25.380 --> 44:30.279
And on the eighth day, God
created this java lava.

44:30.280 --> 44:33.612
<i>Stickiest hash this
side of Lebanon.</i>

44:37.780 --> 44:41.428
Ooh.

44:43.446 --> 44:45.596
