01:07:51.196 --> 01:07:53.494
I'm stalling them, but I
can't hold them off forever.

01:07:53.495 --> 01:07:55.644
Yeah, well, you've got to
do what you've got to do.

01:07:55.645 --> 01:07:59.045
You... you are kidding
me, aren't you?

01:07:59.046 --> 01:08:02.427
Ocean King and drift...
could be the perfect fit.

01:08:02.428 --> 01:08:05.110
Just not right now, Gordon.

01:08:06.295 --> 01:08:08.478
Lots of work to do, mate.

01:08:11.811 --> 01:08:14.345
Well, if you change your mind,
you know where to find me.

01:08:14.346 --> 01:08:16.310
Just don't leave it too long.

01:08:21.228 --> 01:08:23.428
G'day. Can I help you?

01:08:23.429 --> 01:08:24.895
How you goin', mate?

01:08:24.895 --> 01:08:27.428
Looking for a Gus Doran.

01:08:27.429 --> 01:08:28.761
Does he work here?

01:08:28.761 --> 01:08:30.426
That's debatable.

01:08:30.428 --> 01:08:32.060
<i>I got a delivery for him.</i>

01:08:32.062 --> 01:08:35.644
30 blanks.

01:08:35.645 --> 01:08:38.527
- <i>Wanna sign this for me?</i>
- Do I have a choice?

01:08:41.245 --> 01:08:44.210
30 blanks? Thank you, Gus.

01:08:45.261 --> 01:08:47.011
Sorry, man.

01:08:47.013 --> 01:08:49.359
He's killing me.

01:08:59.761 --> 01:09:01.993
Finally emerges.

01:09:03.359 --> 01:09:06.261
Thought I'd lost you
there for a while.

01:09:06.261 --> 01:09:07.859
Hmm?

01:09:11.560 --> 01:09:13.560
Still no sign of Gus.

01:09:13.562 --> 01:09:16.926
It's almost two weeks now.
I'm starting to get worried.

01:09:17.962 --> 01:09:21.060
You know, when I was his age, I
used to disappear for months.

01:09:22.161 --> 01:09:24.643
He'll be fine.

01:09:27.145 --> 01:09:29.611
Yeah, nice seeing you too, J.B.

01:10:17.912 --> 01:10:19.411
Drift surf gear.

01:10:19.412 --> 01:10:21.761
Andy, I found Gus.

01:10:21.762 --> 01:10:26.060
He's, uh... He's real messed up.

01:10:27.294 --> 01:10:29.394
All skin and bone.

01:10:30.811 --> 01:10:32.845
- <i>You still there?</i>
- Yeah.

01:10:32.846 --> 01:10:34.778
<i>He's not good, mate.</i>

01:10:34.779 --> 01:10:36.527
I don't know what to do.

01:10:36.528 --> 01:10:38.960
I'll bring him straight
over, all right?

01:10:41.229 --> 01:10:43.595
Take him to the hospital, Jim.

01:10:43.596 --> 01:10:45.327
Don't bring him here.

01:11:04.577 --> 01:11:06.594
Andy!

01:11:15.744 --> 01:11:18.211
<i>He'll get worse before
he gets better.</i>

01:11:18.212 --> 01:11:20.494
Staring at him won't help.

01:11:42.028 --> 01:11:44.477
<i>Feeling any better?</i>

01:11:44.478 --> 01:11:46.745
Yeah.

01:11:46.746 --> 01:11:49.676
I'm good as gold, mate.

01:11:52.644 --> 01:11:54.378
Do you want anything?

01:11:54.379 --> 01:11:56.844
Yeah yeah.

01:11:59.995 --> 01:12:02.960
Could you take me back with you?

01:12:04.360 --> 01:12:06.761
- Gus...
- Please?

01:12:06.762 --> 01:12:10.861
I don't think I can handle
it out here on my own.

01:12:10.862 --> 01:12:13.777
Ah!

01:12:13.778 --> 01:12:15.644
<i>Yeah, we've been through all that.</i>

01:12:15.645 --> 01:12:17.645
Just stay here, yeah?
Enjoy the zen.

01:12:17.646 --> 01:12:19.444
- Oh, come off it, man.
- What, man?

01:12:19.445 --> 01:12:21.561
Oh, I could just have
a home-cooked meal,

01:12:21.562 --> 01:12:25.894
you know, a proper
lie-down, I'll come good.

01:12:25.895 --> 01:12:27.444
Hey, of course you will, man.

01:12:27.445 --> 01:12:30.895
Do it down here, away
from all the other shit.

01:12:30.896 --> 01:12:33.294
Yeah, well, I'm fine, mate.

01:12:34.861 --> 01:12:37.078
Yeah, you're the perfect
picture of health, man.

01:12:38.879 --> 01:12:42.594
Hey, listen. Hey, hey, hey, hey.

01:12:42.595 --> 01:12:44.427
Tough it out here for the weekend.

01:12:44.428 --> 01:12:45.911
<i>Yeah?</i>

01:12:45.912 --> 01:12:48.394
I'll come back, we'll
go for a wave.

01:12:48.395 --> 01:12:50.843
<i>All right?</i>

01:12:52.111 --> 01:12:54.744
<i>Cool?</i>

01:12:54.745 --> 01:12:56.594
<i>Hmm.</i>

01:12:56.595 --> 01:12:58.460
Yeah, cool, James.

01:13:12.978 --> 01:13:15.961
Saw the light on, thought somebody
might be knocking off the joint.

01:13:15.962 --> 01:13:18.476
Yeah, good luck to him.
There's nothing to steal.

01:13:22.211 --> 01:13:23.510
Hmm.

01:13:23.511 --> 01:13:25.277
Might have missed your calling.

01:13:25.278 --> 01:13:28.844
Well, necessity's the mother of
invention, and all that shit.

01:13:30.878 --> 01:13:33.694
Is he all right?

01:13:33.695 --> 01:13:36.745
He's down the coast. He'll be fine.

01:13:36.746 --> 01:13:38.527
Right.

01:13:44.344 --> 01:13:47.527
You know, it wouldn't kill
you to ask for help, yeah?

01:14:15.211 --> 01:14:16.794
Morning, Mrs. Kelly.

01:14:16.795 --> 01:14:18.344
Good morning, Tom. How are you?

01:14:18.345 --> 01:14:21.461
- Mmm, bit nippy.
- God, it's bloody cold, isn't it?

01:14:36.194 --> 01:14:38.227
What the hell?

01:14:46.177 --> 01:14:48.461
Do you want to come in
and warm up for a bit?

01:14:48.462 --> 01:14:49.928
No, that's really not allowed.

01:14:49.929 --> 01:14:52.160
Well, just come inside for a cuppa

01:14:52.161 --> 01:14:53.761
and then you can get back to it.

01:14:53.762 --> 01:14:55.495
Technically I'm on a stakeout here.

01:14:55.496 --> 01:14:57.544
Oh, for God's sake,
Tom, it's a cup of tea.

01:14:57.545 --> 01:14:59.961
It's hardly hash cookies.

01:14:59.962 --> 01:15:02.744
You still want to know why the
cops trashed our place, did you?

01:15:02.745 --> 01:15:04.644
- Calm down, mate.
- <i>Calm down?!</i>

01:15:04.645 --> 01:15:06.561
There's several kilos
of heroin here.

01:15:06.562 --> 01:15:08.361
There's a cop parked out the front.

01:15:08.362 --> 01:15:10.561
Wonder where he got
the idea from, huh?

01:15:10.562 --> 01:15:13.244
Surfers have been moving their
stuff in boards for years.

01:15:13.245 --> 01:15:14.360
<i>I didn't invent it.</i>

01:15:14.361 --> 01:15:16.227
We should have been clearer
with the fuckin' rules!

01:15:16.228 --> 01:15:19.127
It's not my responsibility,
you fucker!

01:15:19.128 --> 01:15:20.394
<i>Whoa, hang on, hang on, hang on.</i>

01:15:20.395 --> 01:15:22.127
Someone's definitely
gonna miss this.

01:15:22.128 --> 01:15:23.977
Listen, we've got to
help him right now,

01:15:23.978 --> 01:15:26.411
not throw him under
a bus. He's one of us.

01:15:26.412 --> 01:15:29.977
He's a junkie, Jimmy! He's using
our factory to import heroin!

01:15:29.978 --> 01:15:31.977
Have you got that in your head yet?

01:15:31.978 --> 01:15:33.644
Fuck, man, he's family!

01:15:33.645 --> 01:15:36.595
Grow up, Jim! He's put
our family at risk.

01:15:36.596 --> 01:15:38.361
He's put you and me,
mom, everyone at risk,

01:15:38.362 --> 01:15:39.943
everything we've ever
worked for at risk!

01:15:39.944 --> 01:15:41.761
Yeah, you're doing a pretty fuckin'
good job of that all by yourself.

01:15:41.762 --> 01:15:44.376
- Ah!
- <i>Hey!</i>

01:15:51.694 --> 01:15:54.043
You're a real chip off the
old block, aren't you?

01:15:54.044 --> 01:15:56.493
Andy, you there?

01:15:59.127 --> 01:16:01.027
<i>Jim, you all right?</i>

01:16:01.028 --> 01:16:03.360
- Jim?
- <i>Yeah, he's fine.</i>

01:16:03.361 --> 01:16:06.627
Just the planer caught an edge,
whacked him on the nose there.

01:16:11.394 --> 01:16:14.044
Just the whole vibe's
just changed right now.

01:16:14.045 --> 01:16:16.177
- The vibe.
- Peace, brother.

01:16:19.377 --> 01:16:23.061
Hey, I just brought Tom
in for a cup of tea.

01:16:23.062 --> 01:16:26.360
- <i>It's freezing out there.</i>
- One step ahead of you, mom.

01:16:26.361 --> 01:16:29.326
G'day, Tom. Milk, sugar?

01:16:43.761 --> 01:16:45.761
Been looking for you.

01:16:53.762 --> 01:16:55.994
<i>Haven't got all day.</i>

01:16:55.995 --> 01:16:58.211
Yeah, well, you know, maybe
it hasn't come in yet.

01:16:58.212 --> 01:17:00.394
<i>I spoke to the supplier.
It's been delivered.</i>

01:17:00.395 --> 01:17:02.977
Stop wasting my fuckin' time.

01:17:02.978 --> 01:17:05.644
Relax, mate. I'm...

01:17:05.645 --> 01:17:09.661
I'm just saying that you hope...

01:17:09.662 --> 01:17:12.845
I just hope it hasn't been
shaped and sold already...

01:17:12.846 --> 01:17:14.977
Maybe I'm not making myself clear.

01:17:14.978 --> 01:17:17.711
That gear belongs to
some very heavy people.

01:17:17.712 --> 01:17:19.561
Right? There's not much they
won't do to get it back.

01:17:19.562 --> 01:17:22.893
Which puts me in an awkward
position, do you understand?

01:17:22.894 --> 01:17:24.694
Oh, I underst...

01:17:24.695 --> 01:17:26.710
Ah!

01:17:28.227 --> 01:17:29.726
Do you understand?!

01:17:33.977 --> 01:17:36.210
<i>Hmm?</i>

01:17:36.211 --> 01:17:39.027
- Well?
- Okay, yeah. Fair enough.

01:17:39.028 --> 01:17:41.159
Fair enough, yeah.

01:17:42.694 --> 01:17:45.126
I get it.

01:17:48.943 --> 01:17:51.711
I'm sorry, man.

01:17:51.712 --> 01:17:54.193
I took your stuff.

01:17:55.177 --> 01:17:56.644
Excuse me?

01:17:56.645 --> 01:17:59.478
I took your stuff and I
went through it all.

01:17:59.479 --> 01:18:00.993
The lot?

01:18:00.994 --> 01:18:03.460
What, two kilos in
a week, you blew?

01:18:03.461 --> 01:18:06.727
I'm so sorry.

01:18:06.728 --> 01:18:08.611
Don't you fuckin' lie to me!

01:18:08.612 --> 01:18:11.161
Oh! I took it all, you dickhead!

01:18:11.162 --> 01:18:13.827
Do I look like a fuckin'
idiot to you? Hey?!

01:18:20.611 --> 01:18:24.078
Tomorrow you're going to
come bring me my gear.

01:18:24.079 --> 01:18:26.310
Because if you don't, I'm
gonna come back here

01:18:26.311 --> 01:18:29.061
and I won't be as forgiving
next time, do you understand?

01:18:29.062 --> 01:18:30.261
Yeah.

01:18:30.262 --> 01:18:33.060
<i>Oh!</i>

01:18:50.111 --> 01:18:52.177
<i>How's the nose?</i>

01:18:54.479 --> 01:18:57.277
It's still there.

01:18:57.278 --> 01:18:59.710
Well, I guess that's
something, right?

01:19:03.011 --> 01:19:05.610
How did we end up here?

01:19:07.311 --> 01:19:09.977
Welcome to the real world.

01:19:09.978 --> 01:19:12.344
Screw the real world.

01:19:12.345 --> 01:19:15.943
I'm gonna get out of here. I'm
gonna grab Gus and leave,

01:19:15.944 --> 01:19:19.142
go up the coast,
somewhere hard to find.

01:19:21.344 --> 01:19:23.976
Just leave.

01:19:30.544 --> 01:19:33.042
What do you reckon?

01:21:38.760 --> 01:21:41.326
Can I get you a cup of tea, Kat?

01:21:47.127 --> 01:21:49.528
Kat?

01:21:49.529 --> 01:21:51.360
Hey.

01:21:51.361 --> 01:21:56.359
I'm fine. Just a little
bit wobbly today.

01:21:57.727 --> 01:21:59.827
Okay.

01:22:01.260 --> 01:22:03.660
Hey, it'll be all right.

01:22:03.661 --> 01:22:05.827
- I promise.
- Yeah.

01:22:05.828 --> 01:22:08.760
I'm sorry. This is really stupid.

01:22:08.761 --> 01:22:10.993
I'm not usually
like this. I'm fine.

01:22:10.994 --> 01:22:12.727
Cup of tea would be lovely.

01:22:12.728 --> 01:22:14.327
All right.

01:22:14.328 --> 01:22:16.392
Thanks, sweetie.

01:22:51.893 --> 01:22:54.593
Jeez, that's a bugger, isn't it?

01:22:56.927 --> 01:23:00.593
<i>Hello, Andrew. How you holdin' up?</i>

01:23:00.594 --> 01:23:01.860
Me, I'm fine.

01:23:01.861 --> 01:23:04.910
Terrible business, Gus.

01:23:04.911 --> 01:23:07.309
Ah, he was a good kid. I liked him.

01:23:08.510 --> 01:23:11.394
Bet you he'd be pissed off to know
that he's left you in the shit, eh?

01:23:11.395 --> 01:23:13.144
I don't know what you're
talking about, mate.

01:23:13.145 --> 01:23:16.027
Come on, don't waste my time,
mate. It was him who came to me,

01:23:16.028 --> 01:23:18.544
offering to get my product
delivered to your factory.

01:23:18.545 --> 01:23:20.411
That's news to me.

01:23:20.412 --> 01:23:22.377
Oh, well, that's
just a minor detail.

01:23:22.378 --> 01:23:25.810
What's a major fuckin' detail
is it never got to me.

01:23:25.811 --> 01:23:27.593
So now it's real simple...

01:23:27.594 --> 01:23:30.310
You either give me my gear
or you give me my money.

01:23:30.311 --> 01:23:32.177
What do you reckon?

01:23:32.178 --> 01:23:36.277
What about you go and get
fucked, we call it even?

01:23:36.278 --> 01:23:37.727
Hmm?

01:23:38.994 --> 01:23:40.560
Fair enough.

01:23:40.561 --> 01:23:42.892
Ha!

01:23:45.227 --> 01:23:47.477
You know, in some
fucked-up countries,

01:23:47.478 --> 01:23:50.227
they'll chop a bloke's hand off for
stealing another bloke's gear.

01:23:50.228 --> 01:23:51.510
Ah!

01:23:54.927 --> 01:23:56.810
That's a silly place to park.

01:23:56.811 --> 01:23:58.776
I wouldn't do that if I was
you, you fuckin' hippie.

01:23:58.777 --> 01:24:00.626
Take a long time to forgive that.

01:24:00.627 --> 01:24:02.925
I guess we'll cross that
bridge when we come to it.

01:24:03.777 --> 01:24:05.609
Let him go.

01:24:19.677 --> 01:24:21.976
Don't make me ask your mom, Andy.

01:24:27.060 --> 01:24:29.710
You have to go to the police.

01:24:29.711 --> 01:24:31.743
And say what? That I'm in a feud

01:24:31.744 --> 01:24:33.228
with the local bikie
gang over a drug debt?

01:24:33.229 --> 01:24:34.560
Which is not yours.

01:24:34.561 --> 01:24:36.328
It was delivered to my factory.

01:24:36.329 --> 01:24:37.494
I even signed for it.

01:24:37.495 --> 01:24:39.560
Okay, then call Gordon king.

01:24:39.561 --> 01:24:41.810
His offer is pretty
reasonable considering...

01:24:41.811 --> 01:24:43.244
Considering what?

01:24:43.245 --> 01:24:45.211
I do that, then I
become Gordon king.

01:24:45.212 --> 01:24:47.260
You're nothing like him. He
never surfed a day in his life.

01:24:47.261 --> 01:24:49.027
It doesn't matter, Lani!

01:24:49.028 --> 01:24:51.493
We're not selling out.
That's the point.

01:24:51.494 --> 01:24:54.694
Tell her, J.B.

01:24:54.695 --> 01:24:56.127
Tell her.

01:24:56.128 --> 01:24:57.560
<i>She's right.</i>

01:24:57.561 --> 01:25:02.410
Sometimes you got to
exploit the system, yeah,

01:25:02.411 --> 01:25:05.059
<i>or the system's going
to exploit you.</i>

01:25:07.077 --> 01:25:09.510
It's Darwinian, man.

01:25:09.511 --> 01:25:12.744
We adapt, we survive

01:25:12.745 --> 01:25:14.477
and we move on.

01:25:17.961 --> 01:25:21.228
What the fuck are you talking about,
after all we've been through?

01:25:21.229 --> 01:25:24.193
Having come this far?

01:25:41.343 --> 01:25:43.010
<i>Is everything clear?</i>

01:25:43.011 --> 01:25:46.393
Any questions, Kat, feel
free to drop me a line.

01:25:46.394 --> 01:25:51.027
Then sign it and return
it as soon as you can.

01:25:51.028 --> 01:25:53.777
Hello, Andrew.

01:25:53.778 --> 01:25:57.076
You're making a very wise
decision, Mrs. Kelly.

01:26:01.410 --> 01:26:04.143
Mom?

01:26:05.310 --> 01:26:07.210
<i>Hey!</i>

01:26:07.211 --> 01:26:09.693
You really thought I'd
agree to that, did you?

01:26:09.694 --> 01:26:11.793
It's not up to you. The house
is in your mother's name.

01:26:11.794 --> 01:26:13.427
I think you'll find
it's a very fair price.

01:26:13.428 --> 01:26:15.893
What, the exact same amount
we paid for it 12 years ago?

01:26:15.894 --> 01:26:17.693
- The market's been very flat.
- <i>Andy!</i>

01:26:17.694 --> 01:26:20.243
- You thieving prick!
- Andrew, enough!

01:26:22.061 --> 01:26:23.943
Safe travels.

01:26:24.743 --> 01:26:26.960
Andrew, this way we get to pack up

01:26:26.961 --> 01:26:28.527
and start again somewhere new.

01:26:28.528 --> 01:26:30.727
- We're not going anywhere, mom.
- I know about Miller.

01:26:30.728 --> 01:26:32.543
Lani told me. I know
about the whole thing.

01:26:32.544 --> 01:26:34.877
We fought for years to say
that we live here. All right?

01:26:34.878 --> 01:26:38.044
And you're telling me that we're going to
run away with our tail between our legs?

01:26:38.045 --> 01:26:40.193
Without so much as a fight?

01:26:41.493 --> 01:26:44.860
A real fighter knows when to stand
his ground and when to walk away.

01:26:44.861 --> 01:26:48.559
I thought you'd worked
that out by now.

01:26:54.711 --> 01:26:56.927
<i>It'll sort out the bank, it's
gonna take care of Miller.</i>

01:26:56.928 --> 01:26:59.011
Your ankle won't handle it.
Think about it.

01:26:59.012 --> 01:27:01.211
These are pro surfers
from all over the world.

01:27:01.212 --> 01:27:04.244
- You'll be lucky if you even qualify.
- It's $5,000, Lani.

01:27:04.245 --> 01:27:06.060
Which you have zero
chance of winning.

01:27:06.061 --> 01:27:09.710
You think I'm gonna roll over for these
pricks, you've got another thing coming.

01:27:09.711 --> 01:27:11.560
This is real. Miller
is not going away.

01:27:11.561 --> 01:27:13.625
- Exactly!
- Would you stop?

01:27:15.027 --> 01:27:16.260
What?

01:27:16.261 --> 01:27:18.593
You can't fix this on your own.

01:27:18.594 --> 01:27:20.827
Okay? You can't.

01:27:20.828 --> 01:27:22.526
Not this time.

01:27:22.527 --> 01:27:24.760
If Jimmy were here, it might
be a different story.

01:27:24.761 --> 01:27:27.326
Yeah, but Jimmy's not here, is he?

01:27:32.810 --> 01:27:36.959
You know the trouble with
being the last man standing?

01:27:38.660 --> 01:27:41.093
You got no one to share it with.

01:27:46.776 --> 01:27:48.710
<i>Come on, come over here.</i>

01:27:48.711 --> 01:27:50.708
Have a good surf, man.

01:27:52.177 --> 01:27:54.443
- Hey.
- Hey.

01:27:54.444 --> 01:27:56.994
Is this the place to register
for the qualifying events?

01:27:56.995 --> 01:27:58.243
Yeah yeah. What's your name?

01:27:58.244 --> 01:27:59.510
Andrew Kelly.

01:27:59.511 --> 01:28:03.127
Uh, nah, I've got a James Kelly.

01:28:03.128 --> 01:28:05.226
Yeah, that's my brother.

01:28:05.227 --> 01:28:07.127
I just want to compete
in the open qualifiers.

01:28:07.128 --> 01:28:10.710
It's a pro event, so qualifying
heats are invite only.

01:28:10.711 --> 01:28:13.426
- Sorry.
- Price of popularity, I'm afraid.

01:28:13.427 --> 01:28:15.977
Hey, what do you think? Too big?

01:28:15.978 --> 01:28:18.710
She reckons you're not holding an
open qualifying round, Gordon.

01:28:18.711 --> 01:28:21.276
I'm afraid not. Seems
everyone from Sunny down

01:28:21.277 --> 01:28:23.111
wants a crack at the five Gs.

01:28:23.112 --> 01:28:24.843
<i>We are drowning in interest.</i>

01:28:24.844 --> 01:28:26.677
So what difference would
one more make then?

01:28:26.678 --> 01:28:29.176
You scared an unknown
might scoop the pool?

01:28:29.177 --> 01:28:31.809
Jeez.

01:28:34.476 --> 01:28:37.044
You know what?

01:28:37.045 --> 01:28:40.792
It breaks my heart to
see a grown man beg.

01:28:43.944 --> 01:28:46.642
Hey, I can't help you
out there, though.

01:28:52.927 --> 01:28:55.059
Good luck.

01:28:57.043 --> 01:28:59.743
Day one of the Ocean
King qualifying round,

01:28:59.744 --> 01:29:01.377
with some heavy waves out the back,

01:29:01.378 --> 01:29:04.143
connecting right through
to the inside bank here.

01:29:24.944 --> 01:29:26.794
<i>Let's have a look. Big
set coming through here.</i>

01:29:26.795 --> 01:29:30.177
<i>Turning and paddling hard is the
Seacliffe local, Andrew Kelly.</i>

01:29:30.178 --> 01:29:32.844
<i>Oh, it's a very low take-off...
No, he's made the drum!</i>

01:29:32.845 --> 01:29:34.543
<i>He's crashed right
down through the lip!</i>

01:29:34.544 --> 01:29:37.692
<i>Oh, this is tremendous stuff.
He's looking for the pocket.</i>

01:29:41.911 --> 01:29:44.894
<i>Oh, ho ho ho!</i>

01:29:44.895 --> 01:29:47.176
<i>Heavy wipe-out there
from Andrew Kelly!</i>

01:29:47.177 --> 01:29:49.760
<i>Gee whiz, that's not going
to impress the judges.</i>

01:29:49.761 --> 01:29:52.193
<i>I reckon he's already
trailing on the scoreboard.</i>

01:29:52.194 --> 01:29:54.343
Looks to be a little
out of his depth

01:29:54.344 --> 01:29:57.009
<i>in this building
six-to-eight-foot swell.</i>

01:30:01.061 --> 01:30:02.793
<i>There's only seconds
to go now, folks.</i>

01:30:02.794 --> 01:30:05.476
<i>Last chance for one
lucky surfer to step up</i>

01:30:05.477 --> 01:30:08.375
<i>and score enough points to make
it through to the main event.</i>

01:30:31.193 --> 01:30:33.260
<i>Oh, ho! Top stuff!</i>

01:30:33.261 --> 01:30:36.427
<i>Coming from behind to snag
the big wave of the set,</i>

01:30:36.428 --> 01:30:38.627
<i>let's take a look.
Ha ha, he's done it!</i>

01:30:38.628 --> 01:30:41.210
Picking up enough points
on that last ride

01:30:41.211 --> 01:30:43.459
to scrape through to
tomorrow's competition round.

01:30:43.460 --> 01:30:45.726
<i>He's got to be stoked
with that result.</i>

01:30:45.727 --> 01:30:47.810
<i>But with the best surfers
from all over the planet,</i>

01:30:47.811 --> 01:30:49.760
<i>including world #1 Sunny Townsend,</i>

01:30:49.761 --> 01:30:53.027
<i>all lining up for a crack at
the 5,000 bucks first prize,</i>

01:30:53.028 --> 01:30:57.143
<i>well, things just got a lot
tougher for the local lad.</i>

01:31:05.960 --> 01:31:08.359
<i>Thought you said this
place was hard to find.</i>

01:31:08.360 --> 01:31:12.442
Not hard enough, obviously.

01:31:15.544 --> 01:31:17.743
It's like the moon up here.

01:31:17.744 --> 01:31:19.977
You must really love
your own company.

01:31:19.978 --> 01:31:21.343
What's not to love?

01:31:26.944 --> 01:31:29.076
Andy's going to surf the pro,

01:31:29.077 --> 01:31:30.761
bad ankle and all.

01:31:30.762 --> 01:31:33.143
- You serious?
- Mm-hmm.

01:31:33.144 --> 01:31:36.526
Figures he stands a shot
at winning the five grand.

01:31:36.527 --> 01:31:40.276
<i>You know, try and get
Miller off his back.</i>

01:31:40.277 --> 01:31:42.010
Oh.

01:31:42.011 --> 01:31:44.243
Good luck to him.

01:31:44.244 --> 01:31:46.592
Yeah, he'll need it.

01:31:47.360 --> 01:31:49.192
Seen the forecast?

01:31:50.176 --> 01:31:53.060
Big swell due to arrive
at Seacliffe tomorrow.

01:31:53.061 --> 01:31:55.725
Not sure Andy knows
what's about to hit him.

01:31:57.993 --> 01:31:59.776
<i>Here we are, folks, the day
we've been waiting for,</i>

01:31:59.777 --> 01:32:01.410
<i>day one of the main event.</i>

01:32:01.411 --> 01:32:03.594
<i>Get ready to watch the
very best surfers</i>

01:32:03.595 --> 01:32:06.526
<i>from all over the world,
from Hawaii to Peru</i>

01:32:06.527 --> 01:32:10.110
<i>to the U.S. of A., all going head
to head with Australia's best.</i>

01:32:10.111 --> 01:32:12.594
Surfers crossing here.

01:32:12.595 --> 01:32:15.093
Asshole.

01:32:16.194 --> 01:32:18.725
<i>Hey, come on, mate.
Haven't got all day.</i>

01:32:21.076 --> 01:32:23.810
<i>Believe it or not, for once the
weather bureau's got it right.</i>

01:32:23.811 --> 01:32:25.426
<i>The swell's come up overnight,</i>

01:32:25.427 --> 01:32:27.760
<i>and now it looks like the
sea gods are either smiling</i>

01:32:27.761 --> 01:32:31.544
or they're really pissed off,
depending on your persuasion today.

01:32:31.545 --> 01:32:34.743
<i>So anyway, buckle up,
ladies and gentlemen.</i>

01:32:34.744 --> 01:32:37.109
<i>I've got a feeling things
could get real bumpy.</i>

01:32:38.643 --> 01:32:41.760
Didn't know they had
a seniors' comp'.

01:32:41.761 --> 01:32:43.711
Real announcers and everything.

01:32:43.712 --> 01:32:45.376
How long have I been
away for again?

01:32:45.377 --> 01:32:48.160
Jimmy!

01:32:51.560 --> 01:32:53.777
<i>So here we go... Draw
for the first heat today</i>

01:32:53.778 --> 01:32:57.210
is Harris, Cay, Harvey and Kelly.

01:32:57.211 --> 01:33:00.026
You qualified? Fair dinkum?

01:33:00.027 --> 01:33:02.093
<i>All competitors in heat
one, please make your way</i>

01:33:02.094 --> 01:33:03.860
- <i>to the marshalling area now.</i>
- Gotta go.

01:33:03.861 --> 01:33:05.960
Andy?

01:33:05.961 --> 01:33:08.744
I've been surfing perfect
six-footers for the past six weeks.

01:33:08.745 --> 01:33:10.793
You look like you've
been surfing a desk.

01:33:10.794 --> 01:33:12.726
Entries are closed.
They're not gonna let you.

01:33:12.727 --> 01:33:15.476
<i>I've already spoken to them.</i>

01:33:15.477 --> 01:33:20.075
They'll let him surf, but only if
someone else drops out last minute.

01:33:22.210 --> 01:33:26.059
Look, you dragged us
here from day one,

01:33:26.060 --> 01:33:28.559
kicking and screaming.

01:33:29.543 --> 01:33:33.241
Let someone else carry
the load for a while.

01:33:34.043 --> 01:33:35.976
I've got this, brother.

01:33:37.410 --> 01:33:39.459
Trust me.

01:33:54.143 --> 01:33:55.776
<i>Oh, hold onto your hats, folks.</i>

01:33:55.777 --> 01:33:57.760
<i>It's the real deal out there today.</i>

01:33:57.761 --> 01:33:59.143
<i>Whoa!</i>

01:34:02.377 --> 01:34:04.193
<i>There you have one of
those new kook cords</i>

01:34:04.194 --> 01:34:06.892
<i>the lads are using to hold onto
their boards after a wipe-out.</i>

01:34:06.893 --> 01:34:08.777
Can't see 'em catching on,
though, if you ask me.

01:34:08.778 --> 01:34:12.343
<i>I move like a cat,
charge like a ram</i>

01:34:12.344 --> 01:34:14.227
<i>Sting like a bee</i>

01:34:14.228 --> 01:34:17.859
<i>Babe, I wanna be your man...</i>

01:34:17.860 --> 01:34:19.360
<i>Up riding again in yellow</i>

01:34:19.361 --> 01:34:20.892
<i>is the last-minute
substitution, Jimmy Kelly.</i>

01:34:20.893 --> 01:34:22.276
<i>Come on, Jim!</i>

01:34:22.277 --> 01:34:24.410
<i>Well, it's plain to see</i>

01:34:24.411 --> 01:34:26.727
<i>You were meant for me, yeah</i>

01:34:26.728 --> 01:34:30.909
<i>I'm your boy, your
20th century toy...</i>

01:34:33.393 --> 01:34:35.393
<i>Oh, how about that, folks?!</i>

01:34:35.394 --> 01:34:37.610
<i>Ferocious final ride
from young Kelly.</i>

01:34:37.611 --> 01:34:39.743
- <i>Good stuff!</i>
- Ah!

01:34:39.744 --> 01:34:43.009
- <i>Go, Jimmy!</i>
- That's my boy.

01:34:43.010 --> 01:34:45.443
Scorecards are in. You're
not going to believe this.

01:34:45.444 --> 01:34:47.726
Winning his way through
to the big final round

01:34:47.727 --> 01:34:50.059
is the local lad, Jimmy Kelly!

01:34:50.060 --> 01:34:53.009
<i>Let's give it up for Jim.</i>

01:35:02.360 --> 01:35:05.460
<i>It's a shame he's not going to
stick around for the contest.</i>

01:35:05.461 --> 01:35:08.726
<i>He's like a hermit crab...
Wears his house on his back,</i>

01:35:08.727 --> 01:35:11.126
pulls his head in when
he feels bad vibes.

01:35:11.127 --> 01:35:14.092
<i>Hmm, fair enough.</i>

01:35:19.293 --> 01:35:21.793
Would it be okay if I threw
out a blanket apology

01:35:21.794 --> 01:35:24.226
for all the stupid shit
I've said recently?

01:35:29.193 --> 01:35:32.009
Thanks for coming back.

01:35:32.010 --> 01:35:34.176
You still don't get it, do you?

01:35:34.177 --> 01:35:35.276
<i>What?</i>

01:35:35.277 --> 01:35:37.243
God, you're such a dumbass.

01:35:37.244 --> 01:35:39.493
You and Jimmy...

01:35:39.494 --> 01:35:41.643
You're like Yin and Yang.

01:35:41.644 --> 01:35:44.143
One pretty much sucks
without the other.

01:35:44.144 --> 01:35:45.343
I'll take that as a compliment.

01:35:45.344 --> 01:35:46.859
Well, take it however you want.

01:35:46.860 --> 01:35:50.108
- <i>I'll take it as a compliment then.</i>
- Fine, do it.

01:36:07.760 --> 01:36:10.392
This any use to you?

01:36:11.576 --> 01:36:13.759
You fixed it.

01:36:13.760 --> 01:36:16.425
Unreal.

01:36:19.959 --> 01:36:21.693
He'd have liked that.

01:36:26.976 --> 01:36:29.193
- Aww!
- Jim, when you're out there today...

01:36:29.194 --> 01:36:32.343
I already know what you're
gonna say, and I agree.

01:36:32.344 --> 01:36:34.360
"Play it safe, make sure
I get into the final,

01:36:34.361 --> 01:36:36.293
no points for second." All right?

01:36:36.294 --> 01:36:39.309
I was going to say
the exact opposite.

01:36:39.310 --> 01:36:40.976
You're a natural.

01:36:40.977 --> 01:36:42.859
J.B. was right.

01:36:42.860 --> 01:36:45.610
Go for it, man. Get into it.

01:36:45.611 --> 01:36:47.243
It's the whole point, right?

01:36:52.243 --> 01:36:55.477
<i>Oh, jeez, it's not for the
faint-hearted out there today.</i>

01:36:55.478 --> 01:36:57.876
<i>The brunt of the big-storm
swell has arrived.</i>

01:36:57.877 --> 01:37:01.442
Mother nature has really turned
it on for the final, folks.

01:37:05.659 --> 01:37:07.393
<i>A minute to go</i>

01:37:07.394 --> 01:37:09.775
and it looks like it's come
down to a two-man tussle

01:37:09.776 --> 01:37:11.826
<i>between Hawaii's Sunny Townsend</i>

01:37:11.827 --> 01:37:14.742
<i>and Jimmy Kelly.</i>

01:37:14.743 --> 01:37:16.193
<i>Now Kelly's only a
few points behind,</i>

01:37:16.194 --> 01:37:18.460
<i>but really looks to be
outclassed by the Hawaiian,</i>

01:37:18.461 --> 01:37:21.859
<i>who seems to be in a league
of his own out there today.</i>

01:37:21.860 --> 01:37:24.109
<i>Come on, Jimmy!</i>

01:37:25.942 --> 01:37:29.108
Come on, Jimmy.
Get inside him, mate.

01:37:30.675 --> 01:37:32.343
<i>Get inside him!</i>

01:37:32.344 --> 01:37:33.742
Sunny's all over him.

01:37:37.326 --> 01:37:38.510
<i>Oh, this is clinical.</i>

01:37:38.511 --> 01:37:40.209
<i>We are watching a master class</i>

01:37:40.210 --> 01:37:42.275
<i>on competition surfing right now.</i>

01:37:45.093 --> 01:37:47.142
<i>Oh, that's unbelievable!</i>

01:37:47.143 --> 01:37:49.293
<i>Sunny's hit the lip
really hard then, people,</i>

01:37:49.294 --> 01:37:51.143
<i>then floated right across the wave.</i>

01:37:51.144 --> 01:37:52.910
<i>That's ground-breaking stuff there</i>

01:37:52.911 --> 01:37:54.759
<i>from the big-wave
specialist from Maui.</i>

01:37:55.777 --> 01:37:58.910
Ha ha! Hey? How good's this bloke?

01:37:58.911 --> 01:38:03.026
<i>Let's see... with 60
seconds left on the clock,</i>

01:38:03.027 --> 01:38:05.443
<i>and trailing the Hawaiian
on the scoreboard,</i>

01:38:05.444 --> 01:38:07.127
<i>it looks like the local
lad's left his run</i>

01:38:07.128 --> 01:38:09.410
<i>just a bit too late, folks.</i>

01:38:09.411 --> 01:38:11.226
Smile, will ya?!

01:38:11.227 --> 01:38:13.076
Get out of here, you lunatic!

01:38:13.077 --> 01:38:14.692
It's too big. You'll get smashed.

01:38:14.693 --> 01:38:17.609
Not today, my man. Not today.

01:38:19.293 --> 01:38:22.091
Here we go... out the back.

01:38:23.127 --> 01:38:25.059
Hold the phone, people.

01:38:25.060 --> 01:38:26.842
<i>This thing is not over yet.</i>

01:38:32.377 --> 01:38:34.759
Go, Jimbo. Go, son!

01:38:36.892 --> 01:38:39.075
<i>Come on!</i>

01:39:32.126 --> 01:39:35.064
- What do you think you're doing?
- That's my brother out there.

01:39:41.143 --> 01:39:43.659
He's over there!

01:40:26.160 --> 01:40:27.926
Ah!

01:40:34.260 --> 01:40:36.558
You okay, you mad bastard?

01:40:36.559 --> 01:40:39.625
I blew it, man. I'm so sorry.

01:40:49.361 --> 01:40:53.127
Yeah! Yeah!

01:41:00.343 --> 01:41:02.110
<i>How about this kid?!</i>

01:41:03.977 --> 01:41:05.842
Ocean King, folks!

01:41:05.843 --> 01:41:08.609
Ocean King on an Ocean King board.

01:41:47.892 --> 01:41:50.891
Get off the road, everyone.
Get off the road.

01:41:54.043 --> 01:41:56.774
<i>Okay, come on, get off the road.</i>

01:42:01.710 --> 01:42:03.559
<i>I know, right?</i>

01:42:03.560 --> 01:42:05.493
<i>Make sure you come back to us.</i>

01:42:05.494 --> 01:42:08.327
<i>Oh, wait, wait, don't
forget your wax.</i>

01:42:08.328 --> 01:42:10.160
Thanks so much.

01:42:10.161 --> 01:42:11.959
Where have you been?
I've been trying

01:42:11.960 --> 01:42:14.525
- to call you all morning.
- Yeah, we disconnected the phone.

01:42:14.526 --> 01:42:17.143
- Good stuff, mate.
- What is going on here?

01:42:17.144 --> 01:42:19.625
Wait, you guys haven't seen it yet?

01:42:19.626 --> 01:42:21.758
<i>Seen what?</i>

01:42:23.342 --> 01:42:25.093
Front page.

01:42:26.426 --> 01:42:29.991
Oh, Jimmy.

01:42:31.643 --> 01:42:34.726
Jimmy!

01:42:34.727 --> 01:42:38.026
It's been crazy all day.

01:42:38.827 --> 01:42:41.325
Drift Surf Gear.

01:42:41.326 --> 01:42:44.442
Oh, finally, man. The line's been
busy for, like, the last hour.

01:42:44.443 --> 01:42:46.375
Yeah, it's sort of crazy
down here at the moment.

01:42:46.376 --> 01:42:47.608
<i>I imagine.</i>

01:42:47.609 --> 01:42:49.409
T.J. Adleman from the
surf hut in Venice.

01:42:49.410 --> 01:42:51.442
<i>I'm looking at your
photo right now.</i>

01:42:51.443 --> 01:42:53.459
<i>It's a hell of a move, you know
what I'm saying? Hell of a move.</i>

01:42:53.460 --> 01:42:57.160
I already had some guys in here this
morning asking after the boards.

01:42:57.161 --> 01:42:58.775
<i>Hoping I'm not too late
to place an order.</i>

01:42:58.776 --> 01:43:01.476
- No, you're right.
- <i>Great, man, great.</i>

01:43:01.477 --> 01:43:03.942
Why don't we start with,
I don't know, say, 15?

01:43:03.943 --> 01:43:05.259
15?

01:43:05.260 --> 01:43:07.043
Absolutely.

01:43:07.044 --> 01:43:10.210
That's great, man. 15 a month and
then we can take it from there, cool?

01:43:10.211 --> 01:43:13.392
Let me just put you on
to my sales department.

01:43:15.359 --> 01:43:18.358
Uh, Lani Kealoha.

01:43:20.426 --> 01:43:22.074
Grumley?

01:43:23.210 --> 01:43:24.776
I brought the house
contract for you.

01:43:24.777 --> 01:43:26.376
That's terrific, Andrew.

01:43:26.377 --> 01:43:27.808
Yeah.

01:43:33.325 --> 01:43:35.109
Ow.

01:43:35.110 --> 01:43:36.958
Sheree.

01:43:39.926 --> 01:43:42.559
<i>Yep yep, we'll have
some more in next week.</i>

01:43:42.560 --> 01:43:44.509
See you then.

01:43:48.509 --> 01:43:50.574
Hey?

01:44:09.310 --> 01:44:11.542
Looks like a bomb went off.

01:44:11.543 --> 01:44:14.225
Amazing what a little
publicity will do.

01:44:14.226 --> 01:44:17.309
- Yeah.
- Sure you don't want to stick around?

01:44:17.310 --> 01:44:20.476
And become part of the
surfing industrial machine?

01:44:20.477 --> 01:44:24.025
I don't think so.

01:44:28.077 --> 01:44:31.325
Hey, give us a hand.

01:44:33.242 --> 01:44:36.091
Sure.

01:44:37.242 --> 01:44:39.809
Looks like you guys are
off the hook then.

01:44:39.810 --> 01:44:42.143
Well, not completely.

01:44:42.144 --> 01:44:44.143
There's still Miller.

01:44:44.144 --> 01:44:45.943
Oh, right, you didn't hear, no.

01:44:45.944 --> 01:44:48.709
See, apparently someone
tipped off the cops.

01:44:48.710 --> 01:44:50.709
And they raided his
joint last night

01:44:50.710 --> 01:44:53.776
and found a sizeable stash
underneath the bed.

01:44:53.777 --> 01:44:55.609
You serious? What, heroin?

01:44:55.610 --> 01:44:59.342
No, it was high-grade
hash from Indonesia.

01:45:00.643 --> 01:45:03.541
I didn't know he was
into that kind of stuff.

01:45:05.292 --> 01:45:07.791
It's all karma, brother.

01:45:08.359 --> 01:45:10.075
Give 'em.

01:45:11.692 --> 01:45:15.093
So I hear they offered you
a spot on the pro tour.

01:45:15.094 --> 01:45:16.659
Yeah, I'm still not sure about it.

01:45:16.660 --> 01:45:19.392
Man, what are you talking about?

01:45:19.393 --> 01:45:21.692
Huh? Go for it.

01:45:21.693 --> 01:45:23.309
Yeah.

01:45:24.910 --> 01:45:27.826
Just bust 'em wide open.

01:45:27.827 --> 01:45:29.976
<i>Begone!</i>

01:45:29.977 --> 01:45:32.077
Where you going now?

01:45:32.078 --> 01:45:34.409
South.

01:45:34.410 --> 01:45:37.308
Maybe north.

01:45:37.309 --> 01:45:39.392
<i>Maybe, I don't know.</i>

01:45:39.393 --> 01:45:42.259
That's the whole trip right
there, isn't it, man?

01:45:44.559 --> 01:45:47.292
See you when I see you.

01:45:47.293 --> 01:45:49.292
Ha.

01:46:11.376 --> 01:46:15.675
<i>And in the morning I'll be waiting</i>

01:46:17.976 --> 01:46:22.058
<i>For your never-ending wave</i>

